content: That's really interesting. I didn't know that the Maltese Temples of Mnajdra coin had such a low mintage. I've been thinking of expanding my collection to include more coins from smaller EU countries. What's the design like on the 2015 Luxembourg 2-euro coin commemorating the 15th anniversary of the accession to the throne of Grand Duke Henri? Is it a unique design or does it follow a common theme?
